cambridge celta [56] teaching experience if you want to go and do not already have good qualifications, get a tefl (teaching english as a foreign language) certificate. it really helps. there are a fairly strong preferences for native english speakers and for citizens of major english-speaking countries. job ads routinely include a list of acceptable passports; uk, us, canada, australia, and new zealand are on every list, ireland and south africa on most. some schools will not even read the rest of your resume if you do not have one of those passports. various prejudices may also come into play; 